This documents how to setup a Sphinx website.  These instructions are taken from the Sphinx site

    http://sphinx.pocoo.org


(1) Install Sphinx (this assumes a working version of Python is installed on your machine)
  Under Ubuntu.

    ~$ sudo apt-install python-sphinx

  Under OSX and Windows.
  Go to the Python Package index download and install 

    http://pypi.python.org/pypi/Sphinx

(2) Create a Sphinx project
     
    ~$ mkdir www
    ~$ sphinx-quickstart
 
(3) Make and view the default page

    ~$ make html
    ~$ firefox ./_build/html/index.html

Then to add sphinx extension for ipython, numpy and matplotlib follow the directions here

http://matplotlib.sourceforge.net/sampledoc/extensions.html